Healing is re-awakening the best parts of you that were hidden when the trauma happened. How do you re-awaken and discover yourself after trauma? 

1. Therapy 
2. Doing more of what you love and what brings you joy 
3. Joyful movement of any kind 
4. Focusing on being fully present in the present 
5. Disconnecting from technology 
6. Practicing self-regulation through techniques like the Neurocycle, breath work, meditation 

I’ll be doing a podcast on this specific topic of how to re-discover yourself after trauma. Be sure to subscribe to my podcast so you never miss an episode! This is not to say you should run away from fears, but there is a big difference between facing fears as part of your growth, and putting yourself in situations (or taking in extra burdens) that are not right for you. You will know the difference when you start to really tune into your emotional and physical warning signals which comes from practicing self-awareness and mind-management. You will sometimes fail to correctly listen to the signals, but with practice it will come more easily! 

I discuss how to learn how to mind-manage and become more self-aware through self-regulation in length in my new book Cleaning up Your Mental Mess! Get your copy wherever books are sold or visit: https://www.cleaningupyourmentalmess.com (tap the link in my bio)

node.text: It’s not the emotions that often cause the problem or profiling suffering. It’s how we respond to the uncomfortable emotions, whether that be by trying to suppress and avoid, indulge in assumptions, or harshly judge the feelings. When you choose to honor your feelings by giving them space and trying to find out why they exist, you will move through them quicker and the results will be more sustainable.
